AS top pupils celebrated yesterday, Free State Education MEC Tate Makgoe played guitar at the event for the top 100 schools and pupils at Central University of Technology, Bloemfontein. Top achiever Neema Masinde (18) said: “ I’m going to study medicine.” Second best performer Gladys Khahlane (18) said she’ll be doing the same. POVERTY PUSHED SENZO TO WORK HARD! Top pupil Siyamthanda Prudent got full marks for science. Best special needs pupil Tiyani Mbedzani (19) said: “I come from a poor background without learning equipment.” Top performer Alycia Ganyane (17) said: “I will be studying computer engineering,”